# Claude Code config — sync repo
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING by default (secrets, sessions, caches, machine-local
# state), then explicitly re-include only the portable config worth syncing.

/*

# Defense-in-depth: never track the auth token, even if the rules above change.
.credentials.json

# --- Tracked config (portable across machines) ---
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/CLAUDE.md
!/settings.base.json
!/settings.machine.wsl.json
!/settings.machine.windows.json
!/scripts
!/.gitattributes
!/roo-to-claude.md
!/skills
!/agents
!/commands
!/hooks
!/keybindings.json
!/multiagent


# Note: settings.local.json is intentionally NOT tracked — it's for machine-local overrides.
